                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bihar leaders to meet PM
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                            Manmohan Singh, Nitish Kumar: Can they bring peace?                                
	Patna, Oct. 26: Bihar chief minister Nitish Kumar would lead an all-party delegation to meet Prime Minister Manmohan Singh at 5pm tomorrow on the issue of the repeated assault on the people of Bihar in Maharashtra.        
	Nitish convened an all-party meeting here which decided to meet the Prime Minister to press for the latters invention to ensure rule of law in Maharashtra.        
	Raj Thackerays Maharashtra Navnirman Sangh-sponsored repeated assault on the people from Hindi heartland in Maharashtra triggered violent backlash in Bihar with students hitting the streets and attacking railway and government property.        
	The violent unrest in the state has become the cause of common concern for Bihars political bigwigs, as the all-party delegation is likely include all state Union ministers, including Lalu Prasad, Ram Vilas Paswan, Raghuvansh Prasad Singh besides senior representatives of all the parties. The senior leaders, cutting across party lines, have unanimously demanded strong action against Raj for fomenting regional hatred by constantly launching assault on non-Marathi people.                                                                                                                                                                         
